Presentation on [Crafting Rails Applications: Expert Practices for Everyday Rails Development](http://www.amazon.com/Crafting-Rails-Applications-Development-Programmers/dp/1934356735/ref=wl_it_dp_v_S_nC?ie=UTF8&coliid=I9J4XAYHBBMGA&colid=K7D6CDDMZG6S)

Note to self: when using showoff and heroku, remember these steps for deploying to Heroku:

- heroku create crafting-rails
- bundle install
- git add Gemfile Gemfile.lock config.ru
- git commit -m 'herokuized'
- git push heroku master

This fixes the Heroku error `Failed to install gems via Bundler. Heroku push rejected, failed to compile Ruby/rack app`